# Context7 MCP Server - MANDATORY USAGE

## 🚨 CRITICAL RULE: ALWAYS USE CONTEXT7 FOR LIBRARY DOCUMENTATION

### What is Context7?

Context7 MCP server provides up-to-date code documentation for LLMs and AI code editors. It ensures you get the latest, accurate information about libraries and frameworks instead of outdated or generic examples.

**Repository**: https://github.com/upstash/context7

### ✅ MANDATORY: Use Context7 for ANY Library/Framework Questions

```typescript
// When you need help with ANY library, ALWAYS use Context7 first
// Examples of when to use Context7:

// ✅ Next.js documentation
'use context7 to get the latest Next.js 15 App Router documentation';

// ✅ Supabase integration patterns
'use context7 to get current Supabase authentication patterns with @supabase/ssr';

// ✅ Prisma ORM usage
'use context7 to get latest Prisma client patterns and best practices';

// ✅ Tailwind CSS v4 configuration
'use context7 to get Tailwind CSS v4 @theme directive usage examples';

// ✅ shadcn/ui component implementation
'use context7 to get current shadcn/ui component patterns and API';

// ✅ TanStack Table integration
'use context7 to get latest @tanstack/react-table examples with shadcn/ui';

// ✅ Recharts configuration
'use context7 to get current recharts patterns for Next.js 15';
```

### Auto-Invoke Rule for Cursor/Windsurf

Add this rule to your `.windsurfrules` file or Cursor Settings > Rules:

```
[[calls]]
match = "when the user requests code examples, setup or configuration steps, or library/API documentation"
tool  = "context7"
```

This will automatically invoke Context7 on any code-related conversation without needing to type anything extra.

### Library ID Quick Reference

For faster access, use specific Context7 library IDs in your prompts:

```typescript
// Core Dependencies
'use library /vercel/next.js for Next.js 15 documentation';
'use library /supabase/supabase for Supabase client patterns';
'use library /prisma/prisma for Prisma ORM examples';
'use library /tailwindlabs/tailwindcss for Tailwind CSS v4';
'use library /shadcn-ui/ui for shadcn/ui components';
'use library /tanstack/table for TanStack Table patterns';
'use library /recharts/recharts for chart components';
```

